==English==
===Noun===
'''Alaric'''

===Etymology===
{{Norse}} Everyone's King

# Alaric I (~370-410), ruler of the Visigoths from 395 until his death (most likely due to fever) in 410.  In 394 he allied with Rome and led the Visigoths in a campaign against the Huns.  After the death of Emperor Theodosius in 395, Alaric led the Visigoths on a campaign across the Empire, finally attacking Italy and sacking Rome in 410.
# Alaric II (???-507), peaceful eighth king of the Visigoths and son of Euric was ruler from 484-507.  Mainly known for his adhearence to Arianism, his surrender to Clovis I in 486, and his compilation of the {w Breviary of Alaric}.